editorialSummary.text: This NYC outpost of a Swedish bakery chain serves up favorites like cardamom & cinnamon buns.

originalText.text: Best cinnamon buns ever. Every time I go to NYC, I need to go there and enjoy this amazing Swedish pastry. This is the only place I've found where the bun is exactly like I like. Not too sweet or too fat, it's just a perfection. Also, the service is always great, no matter if it's busy or not and the place is really cute.

Didnâ€™t have to go to Sweden to have a well-made Cardamom Bun. It had a perfect amount of sweetness for me and the bunâ€™s texture had a good amount of chew in it. Same with the cinnamon bun.

Best to come when they are freshly made as I figured it would be softer and extra fragrant.

The hot chocolate was decadently dark. The coffee was alright. It was darker than my usual preference but pairs well with the buns.

The staff were nice as well.

originalText.text: I am a baker and I fall in love with Fabrique. The cardamom buns hands down the best in the city- the cardamom grinds are very right-front and center. Try cardamom almond cream buns and you are up to a big surprise. I love how the buns is bien cuit and crispy on top. The almond cream portion is generous mixing with peppery cardamom. The saffron raisin buns are worth mentioning too, so aromatic. Lastly, the crispy bread is addictively yummy. Bravo! I

originalText.text:
Possibly the best cardamom bun in the city! I might've enjoyed the almond cardamom bun even more, considering it has the rich cardamom flavor plus yummy frangipane; only downside was it wasn't quite as soft as the regular cardamom bun.
Staff here were great and there was plenty of seating on a rainy Sunday afternoon.

originalText.text:
Updated 10/29/2023
Fabrique continues to dazzle with their bakes. The Seasonal Apple Buns are yummy. The Seeded Crackers are addictive and full of flavor. The Vegan Chocolate Cookie Flats are magical. A  flat square cookie sprinkled with crunchy pearl sugar simply melts in your mouth, delivering a sort of luscious chocolate brownie taste experience. Buy a couple as they freeze beautifully and pulll one out when you are having a chocolate emergency.

This Swedish import is hands down a "must experience" in NYC.

Known for their beautiful and delicious "Buns" after tasting them, you'll understand the line to get in.

We might call them Danish or Pastry in the US. At Fabrique, they're Buns.

The highlight is the Cardamon Bun and the seasonal Saffron Bun. But seriously, everything we've ever tried was delightful ðŸ˜Š.
